"{{Short description|none}}\n<!-- \"none\" is preferred when the title is sufficiently descriptive; see [[WP:SDNONE]] -->\n{{Use mdy dates|date=June 2022}}\n{{Politics of Chad}}\n\nThe '''foreign relations of Chad''' are significantly influenced by the desire for oil revenue and investment in Chadian oil industry and support for former [[Chadian President]] [[Idriss Déby]]. Chad is officially [[Neutral country|non-aligned]] but maintains close relations with [[France]], its former colonial power.{{Update inline|date=September 2023}} Relations with neighbouring countries [[Libya]] and [[Sudan]] vary periodically. Lately, the Idris Déby regime waged an intermittent [[proxy war]] with Sudan. Aside from those two countries, Chad generally enjoys good relations with its neighbouring states.\n\n==Diplomatic relations==\nList of countries which Chad maintains diplomatic relations with:\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! colspan=\"3\" |[[File:Diplomatic_relations_of_Chad.svg|frameless|425x425px]]\n|-\n!#\n!Country\n!Date\n|-\n|1\n|{{flag|United States}}\n|{{Dts|11 August 1960}}<ref>{{Cite web |title=All Countries |url=https://history.state.gov/countries/all |access-date=12 November 2021 |website=Office of the Historian}}</ref>\n|-\n|2\n|{{flag|Germany}}\n|{{dts|11 August 1960}}<ref>{{Cite web |title=Tschad: Steckbrief |url=https://www.auswaertiges-amt.de/de/service/laender/tschad-node/steckbrief-225758 |website=Auswärtiges Amt |access-date=6 March 2025 |language=de}}</ref>\n|-\n|3\n|{{flag|France}}\n|{{Dts|12 August 1960}}<ref>{{Cite journal |title=Liste Chronologique des Ambassadeurs, Envoyés Extraordinaires, Ministres Plénipotentiaires et Chargés D'Affaires de France à L'Étranger Depuis 1945 |url=https://www.diplomatie.gouv.fr/IMG/pdf/maep0035-0120_cle8a5377.pdf |journal=Diplomatie.gouv.fr |language=fr |access-date=15 December 2023}}</ref>\n|-\n|4\n|{{flag|Philippines}}\n|{{DTS|22 September 1960}}<ref>{{Cite web |date=22 September 2018 |title=Today, September 22, we cele